<!-- The Arc -->
<section class="section" id="arc">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="section-title">The Numbers</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">From neuroscience to enterprise product to clinical practice to AI and agentic systems &mdash; my work has always circled a central question: <strong>what actually drives human behavior?</strong></p>
    <div class="arc-interactive">

      <div class="arc-steps">
        <div class="arc-step active" data-step="stanford">
          <div class="arc-step-num">01</div>
          <div class="arc-step-info">
            <div class="arc-step-title">Stanford</div>
            <div class="arc-step-body">Biological Sciences · Beckman Scholar · Published researcher</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="arc-step" data-step="enterprise">
          <div class="arc-step-num">02</div>
          <div class="arc-step-info">
            <div class="arc-step-title">Enterprise Product</div>
            <div class="arc-step-body">Apple · Intuit · Realtor.com · Capital One · 100M+ users</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="arc-step" data-step="clinical">
          <div class="arc-step-num">03</div>
          <div class="arc-step-info">
            <div class="arc-step-title">Clinical Practice</div>
            <div class="arc-step-body">Founded Healify · Somatic therapist · 1M+ assessments</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="arc-step" data-step="agentic">
          <div class="arc-step-num">04</div>
          <div class="arc-step-info">
            <div class="arc-step-title">Agentic AI</div>
            <div class="arc-step-body">Built HabitualOS · Production since 2025 · Daily use</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="arc-success-pane">
        <div class="arc-success-panel active" data-step="stanford">
          <p class="arc-success-label">The foundation</p>
          <p class="arc-success-headline">Ranked first in class, published studies.</p>
          <p class="arc-success-body">I study neuroscience and cognitive science, and won a Beckman Scholarship. The scientific method became a permanent lens for me, not just in research, but for how I develop product and work with people every day. I spend a lot of time looking at problems from different angles, always seeking ways to measure impact.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="arc-success-panel" data-step="enterprise">
          <p class="arc-success-label">The impact</p>
          <p class="arc-success-headline">$45M in incremental revenue. 300% ROI increase. 20% fewer support calls.</p>
          <p class="arc-success-body">Fifteen years embedded at Apple, Intuit, Realtor.com, and Capital One. Products shipped to tens of millions of people, with outcomes documented and measured. The work was real, the numbers were audited — and the through-line was always the same question.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="arc-success-panel" data-step="clinical">
          <p class="arc-success-label">The insight</p>
          <p class="arc-success-headline">1M+ mood assessments. 100+ patients. One unexpected lesson.</p>
          <p class="arc-success-body">After founding Healify and treating patients directly as a somatic therapist, I learned what no user research method had taught me: resistance isn't a design problem. It's a body problem. That insight changed everything about how I build.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="arc-success-panel" data-step="agentic">
          <p class="arc-success-label">The system</p>
          <p class="arc-success-headline">In production daily since 2025.</p>
          <p class="arc-success-body">HabitualOS is a multi-agent system I built for myself — and use every single day. Every failure mode I hit became a design constraint. Every friction point became a feature requirement. There's no shortcut to product-market fit as reliable as being the actual user.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

